2001-03-13  Andreas Kloeckner  <ak@ixion.net>

	* src/js_instruction.cc: prevented identifier redeclaration

	* javascript code: cleanups, added constness
          !!!CAUTION!!! This breaks binary and source compatibility
          All calls to make[Constant]Int/Float/String must be changed
          to makeConstant() or makeValue(). This is a good thing(tm) :)
	  Further, all calls that formerly included a "want_lvalue" 
          parameter have this parameter removed. Remove it also, or
	  else virtual function lookup will fail to find your 
          overrided functions!

	* configure.in: bumped version to 0.95.0
	  also bumped up interface version of shared library, to 
	  guarantee breaking binary compatibility and forcing recompiles
	  (as otherwise strange segfaults may result)

